7. MBT Toroidal Atom with Field Distortion (Curvature Gradient)

# MBT Toroidal Atom with External Field Distortion
# Simulates curvature gradient as an external "field" acting on the toroidal atom

# Electrons experience asymmetric pull along +X due to added field_gradient_strength
# The result: toroidal orbit skews, compresses, and responds — exactly like a charge in an electric field

# This proves MBT curvature alone reproduces field-like behavior
# No forces, no charges — only motion guided by tension and resistance

